# API Conventions: {{ display_name }}

This document defines the conventions all API endpoints in **{{ display_name }}** must follow. Consistency here reduces consumer confusion and makes the API predictable.

---

## URL Structure

### Base URL

All API routes are prefixed with `/api/v1`. Versioning is path-based.

```
https://api.example.com/api/v1/...
```

### Resource Naming

| Convention | Example |
|------------|---------|
| Plural nouns for collections | `/api/v1/users` |
| Singular noun for a resource | `/api/v1/users/{id}` |
| Kebab-case for multi-word resources | `/api/v1/api-keys` |
| Nested resources for ownership | `/api/v1/users/{userId}/orders` |
| Actions as sub-resources (not verbs in URL) | `/api/v1/users/{id}/password-reset` (POST) |

### HTTP Methods

| Method | Semantics | Success Status |
|--------|-----------|---------------|
| `GET` | Read a resource or collection | 200 |
| `POST` | Create a new resource | 201 |
| `PUT` | Full replacement of a resource | 200 |
| `PATCH` | Partial update of a resource | 200 |
| `DELETE` | Remove a resource | 204 |

Never use `GET` for operations that mutate state. Never use `POST` for a read if a `GET` with query parameters will do.

---

## Request Format

### Content-Type

All requests with a body must include:

```
Content-Type: application/json
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
API Platform also accepts `application/ld+json` and `application/vnd.api+json`. Default to `application/json` for simplicity unless JSON-LD or JSON:API features are required.

{% endif %}
### Request Body

Use camelCase for JSON property names:

```json
{
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "firstName": "Jane",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "roleIds": [1, 2]
}
```

### Query Parameters

Use camelCase for query parameter names:

```
GET /api/v1/users?page=1&itemsPerPage=25&orderBy=createdAt&orderDir=desc
GET /api/v1/orders?status=pending&createdAfter=2024-01-01
```

---

## Response Format

### Success Response

For single resources:

```json
{
    "id": "018e1234-5678-7abc-def0-1234567890ab",
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "firstName": "Jane",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "createdAt": "2024-03-15T10:30:00+00:00",
    "updatedAt": "2024-03-15T10:30:00+00:00"
}
```

For collections:

```json
{
    "items": [...],
    "total": 142,
    "page": 1,
    "itemsPerPage": 25
}
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
API Platform's default collection format includes `hydra:member`, `hydra:totalItems`, and pagination links. Use this unless the consumer explicitly needs a plain JSON envelope.

{% endif %}

### Date and Time Format

All timestamps use **ISO 8601** with timezone offset:

```
"createdAt": "2024-03-15T10:30:00+00:00"
```

- Always include timezone information
- Store and return UTC; let consumers convert to local time
- Date-only values use `YYYY-MM-DD` format: `"birthDate": "1990-05-20"`

### Identifiers

Primary keys exposed in the API are **UUIDs** (version 7 preferred for sortability):

```
"id": "018e1234-5678-7abc-def0-1234567890ab"
```

Never expose database auto-increment integers as external IDs. Internal integer IDs remain in the database only.

---

## Error Responses

All error responses follow RFC 7807 (Problem Details for HTTP APIs):

```json
{
    "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/validation",
    "title": "Validation Failed",
    "status": 422,
    "detail": "The request data is invalid.",
    "violations": [
        {
            "propertyPath": "email",
            "message": "This value is not a valid email address.",
            "code": "bd79c0ab-ddba-46cc-a703-a7a4b08de310"
        },
        {
            "propertyPath": "password",
            "message": "This value is too short. It should have 8 characters or more.",
            "code": "9ff3fdc4-b214-49db-8718-39c315e33d45"
        }
    ]
}
```

### Standard Error Types

| HTTP Status | `type` slug | When to use |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| 400 | `bad-request` | Malformed JSON, missing required header |
| 401 | `unauthorized` | Missing or invalid authentication credentials |
| 403 | `forbidden` | Authenticated but not allowed to access this resource |
| 404 | `not-found` | Resource does not exist |
| 409 | `conflict` | Duplicate resource (e.g., email already in use) |
| 422 | `validation` | Request body fails validation constraints |
| 429 | `rate-limit-exceeded` | Too many requests |
| 500 | `internal-error` | Unexpected server error (no detail exposed to client) |

**Rule:** Never expose stack traces, SQL errors, or internal paths in error responses in `prod` environment.

