## Validation

Symfony Validator is the canonical validation layer. Constraints live on:

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
1. The API resource class (using `#[Assert\...]` attributes)
2. DTO classes for write operations (preferred for complex input shapes)
{% else %}
1. Entity classes for persistence-level constraints
2. DTO/Form classes for HTTP input validation (preferred; keep entities clean of HTTP concerns)
{% endif %}

### Common Constraints

```php
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraints as Assert;

final class CreateUserInput
{
    #[Assert\NotBlank]
    #[Assert\Email(mode: 'html5')]
    public string $email;

    #[Assert\NotBlank]
    #[Assert\Length(min: 8, max: 72)]
    public string $password;

    #[Assert\NotBlank]
    #[Assert\Length(max: 100)]
    public string $firstName;

    #[Assert\Choice(choices: ['admin', 'user', 'viewer'])]
    public string $role = 'user';
}
```

Validation errors are automatically formatted as 422 responses with the `violations` structure above.

