## Serialization Groups

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
API Platform uses Symfony Serializer groups declared on the `#[ApiResource]` attribute.

{% endif %}
Standard group naming convention:

| Group | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `{resource}:read` | Default GET response (single resource) |
| `{resource}:list` | Slimmer subset for collection responses (omit large fields) |
| `{resource}:write` | Accepted on POST/PUT/PATCH |
| `{resource}:admin` | Additional fields visible only to admins |
| `{resource}:embed` | Minimal fields when this resource is embedded in another |

```php
use Symfony\Component\Serializer\Annotation\Groups;

class User
{
    #[Groups(['user:read', 'user:list', 'user:embed'])]
    public string $id;

    #[Groups(['user:read', 'user:list'])]
    public string $email;

    #[Groups(['user:read'])]
    public \DateTimeImmutable $createdAt;

    #[Groups(['user:admin'])]
    public string $internalNotes;

    // Write-only: never exposed in responses
    #[Groups(['user:write'])]
    public string $password;
}
```

