## Filtering and Sorting

### Filtering

Filters are passed as query parameters using the field name:

```
GET /api/v1/users?status=active&role=admin
GET /api/v1/orders?createdAfter=2024-01-01&createdBefore=2024-12-31
GET /api/v1/products?name=widget   # partial match
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
Use API Platform's built-in filters:

```php
#[ApiFilter(SearchFilter::class, properties: [
    'email' => 'exact',
    'firstName' => 'partial',
    'status' => 'exact',
])]
#[ApiFilter(DateFilter::class, properties: ['createdAt'])]
#[ApiFilter(RangeFilter::class, properties: ['price'])]
#[ApiFilter(BooleanFilter::class, properties: ['isActive'])]
```

{% endif %}

### Sorting

```
GET /api/v1/users?orderBy=createdAt&orderDir=desc
GET /api/v1/users?orderBy=lastName&orderDir=asc
```

Only explicitly whitelisted fields can be used for sorting. Attempting to sort by a non-whitelisted field returns 400.

