{% if use_auth %}
## Authentication in API Requests

{% if auth_method == "jwt" %}
All protected endpoints require a JWT in the `Authorization` header:

```
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.eyJz...
```

Obtaining a token:

```
POST /api/auth/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "password": "s3cr3t"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9...",
    "refreshToken": "a1b2c3d4...",
    "expiresIn": 3600
}
```

Refresh:

```
POST /api/auth/token/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refreshToken": "a1b2c3d4..."
}
```

{% elif auth_method == "api-key" %}
All protected endpoints require an API key header:

```
X-API-Key: sk_live_abc123...
```

Keys are issued per client and can be revoked independently. Rate limits are applied per key.

{% elif auth_method == "oauth2" %}
All protected endpoints require a Bearer token obtained via OAuth2:

```
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```

Consult the OAuth2 authorization server documentation for token acquisition flows.

{% endif %}

### Unauthenticated Responses

Missing credentials return `401 Unauthorized`. Insufficient permissions return `403 Forbidden`. Never return `404` to hide the existence of a resource from unauthorized users unless the security model explicitly requires it.

{% endif %}

