## Rate Limiting

Rate limits are enforced per authenticated identity (user ID or API key).

| Tier | Limit |
|------|-------|
| Default | 300 requests / minute |
| Write operations (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE) | 60 requests / minute |
| Auth endpoints | 10 requests / minute |

Rate limit information is included in every response:

```
X-RateLimit-Limit: 300
X-RateLimit-Remaining: 297
X-RateLimit-Reset: 1710499200
```

When the limit is exceeded, the response is `429 Too Many Requests` with a `Retry-After` header.

